        <abstract>
            <p>Comments on the great extent of variations and on the acknowledgment of the new idea of greater female variety.</p>
            <p>Expresses belief that the glacial period did affect the tropics, though HWB’s arguments have confounded him.</p>
            <p>Poses a series of questions concerning sexual selection.</p>
        </abstract>
